summary: In this blog post, I share my experience benchmarking several LLMs using the new Marimo Pair skill for a data analysis task. I tested models like Claude Opus, Sonnet, GLM-5.1, and others, evaluating their performance, cost, and adherence to coding instructions. Some models excelled, while others struggled with basic requirements. Curious to see which models stood out and what lessons I learned from this experiment?
---
